values:
Wow, I'm kind of frustrated. First of all, he hasn't called me in two days. Yesterday I understand, because he knows I had to work and I know his circumstances, but today? I don't know. I just hope he calls me tomorrow, or else I'm going to be upset. But moving on...
So why do people think that the world revolves around them, and everyone else needs to work thier shedules around them? OK, let me explain a little. My aunt and uncle, who have a daughter thats about 4 or 5, want to get together with everyoe for Christmas, before Christmas. Ok, no problem really, but thier reason? They dont want thier precious little girl to have to have to leave her new toys at home, because she's going to want to play with them...Wow, I cant wait until shes older, and expects the world to bow down to her. That'ss be intresting.
Eh, just my rant for the night...
more to come when I'm in the writing mood.
